                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                           (115283, 0, 'Thread Lift Aftercare Advice', 'Important aftercare information', '<!DOCTYPE html>\n<html>\n<head>\n</head>\n<body>\n<h2 style=\"text-align: center;\"><span style=\"text-decoration: underline;\"><strong><img src=\"https://crm.pabau.com/cdn/template_archive/3263/template_attachments/9cb3f8738b3ff0edf44d2f46eebab042.jpg\" alt=\"\" width=\"260\" height=\"134\" /><br /><br />Important aftercare information following your thread lift procedure<br /></strong></span></h2>\n<p><strong>&nbsp;</strong></p>\n<h3>A cold compress may gently be applied if required following your procedure<br /><br />The application of make-up MUST be avoided for at least 24 hours, and following this period it is essential that you are careful and mindful of the threads during application<br /><br />When washing the face, care must be taken, and face creams and lotions must be avoided for 24 hours.<br /><br />Facial movements must be restricted for the next 1-3 weeks<br /><br />Hot drinks&nbsp;should be avoided for 48 hours<br /><br />Hard foods which require a lot of chewing must be avoided for 1-3 weeks<br /><br /><strong>Remain upright either sitting or standing for as long as possible and sleep with 3 pillows at night for at least 7 nights. This is especially important when the lips or eye region have been treated. Do not sleep with pressure on the face</strong><br /><br /><strong>Strenuous exercise is to be avoided</strong><br /><br /><strong>SPF30 must be gently applied each day in order to avoid post-inflammatory hyperpigmentation&nbsp;for at least 3 weeks</strong><br /><br /><strong>Avoid dental appointments as well as facial appointments as facial and mouth movements should be restricted for at least 4 weeks</strong><br /><br /><strong>Paracetamol&nbsp;may be taken, but NSAIDs&nbsp;such as Ibuprofen should be avoided for 7 days.</strong><br /><br /><strong>Alcohol must not be consumed for 3-7 days after treatment</strong><br /><br /><strong>Heat treatments such as sauna and sun beds must be avoided for 7 days.&nbsp;<br /></strong><strong><br />Hold your face with your hands if crying, laughing, coughing or sneezing to avoid excessive use of facial muscles<br /></strong><br />You may commence bathing the day after the procedure, taking care not to stretch the face or neck<br /><strong><br />Do not drink with a straw</strong>&nbsp;as this distorts the facial muscles</h3>\n<h3>&nbsp;</h3>\n<h3>&nbsp;</h3>\n<p><span style=\"font-size: 14px;\"><strong>After treatment it is expected that you will see some improvement immediately however there will be a reasonable amount of swelling. The final result will not be evident until at least 8-12 weeks after the procedure.&nbsp;</strong></span><br /><br /><span style=\"font-size: 14px;\"><strong>If bruising is going to occur, following your treatment it is usually apparent at day&nbsp;2-3&nbsp;and will typically resolve over&nbsp;10 days.</strong></span><br /><br /><span style=\"font-size: 14px;\"><strong>It is normal to have a degree of swelling and oedema after your treatment. This usually takes around a 2 weeks to resolve, however it can take longer than this and it is not unusual to have residual swelling for up to a month.</strong></span><br /><br /><span style=\"font-size: 14px;\"><strong>Should you experience any unexpected side effects or any that concern you, please contact the clinic on 01257 367460 as soon as possible.</strong></span></p>\n<p><span style=\"font-size: 14px;\"><strong>&nbsp;</strong></span></p>\n<p><span style=\"font-size: 14px;\"><strong>What to watch out for after treatment</strong></span></p>\n<p><span style=\"font-size: 14px;\">&nbsp;</span></p>\n<ul>\n<li><span style=\"font-size: 14px;\">If you notice any skin colour changes, such as an area of skin becoming purple or red, or experience bruising which appears abnormal, please <strong>contact the clinic immediately</strong></span></li>\n<li><span style=\"font-size: 14px;\">If you notice an <strong><em>increase</em></strong> in pain in the area treated in the days after your procedure, <strong>please contact the clinic immediately</strong></span></li>\n<li><span style=\"font-size: 14px;\">If you notice a sudden relapse or asymmetry in the face, <strong>please contact the clinic immediately</strong></span></li>\n<li><span style=\"font-size: 14px;\">If a bump appears on the face where a thread was trimmed, <strong>please contact the clinic immediately</strong></span></li>\n<li><span style=\"font-size: 14px;\">If you suspect an infection, <strong>please contact the clinic immediately</strong></span></li>\n</ul>\n<p><span style=\"font-size: 14px;\">&nbsp;</span></p>\n<h3>&nbsp;</h3>\n<p><span style=\"font-size: 14px;\">&nbsp;</span></p>\n<p><span style=\"font-size: 14px;\"><strong><br /><br /><br /></strong></span></p>\n<strong><br /><br /></strong><strong><br /><br /></strong>\n</body>\n</html>', 0, 'email', '0000-00-00 00:00:00', '0000-00-00 00:00:00', 0, 0, 0, '', '', 0, 'aftercare', '', '', 0, 0),
