                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                           (131516, 0, 'Injectables Consent', '', '<!DOCTYPE html>\n<html>\n<head>\n</head>\n<body>\n<div style=\"text-align: center;\">\n<table style=\"height: 693px; margin-left: auto; margin-right: auto;\" width=\"917\">\n<tbody>\n<tr>\n<td style=\"text-align: left;\" width=\"301\">\n<p><strong><img src=\"https://crm.pabau.com/cdn/template_archive//template_attachments/4ecaf43824599bc35fee0bf28b8f0704.png\" alt=\"\" width=\"88\" height=\"71\" />BOTOX<sup>&reg;</sup> Consent Form</strong></p>\n<p>BOTOX<sup>&reg;</sup> is a brand name for botulinum toxin type A, a neurotoxin that blocks muscle contraction by temporarily inactivating the nerves that control them.&nbsp; The effects of BOTOX<sup>&reg;</sup> become apparent 2 &ndash; 5 days after the injection, stabilising at 2 weeks, and generally last 3 &ndash; 4 months.</p>\n<p>&nbsp;Unwanted side effects of BOTOX<sup>&reg;</sup> include but are not limited to;</p>\n<ul>\n<li>Local bleeding</li>\n<li>Bruising</li>\n<li>Headache (temporary &ndash; usually 30 minutes)</li>\n<li>Undercorrection (not enough effect) or overcorrection (too much effect)</li>\n<li>Facial asymmetry (one side looks different than the other)</li>\n<li>Injury/ injection of deeper structures/ eyeball</li>\n<li>Paralysis of a nearby muscle leading to: droopy eyelid, double vision, inability to close the eye, difficulty whistling or drinking from a straw (if injections around the mouth)</li>\n<li>Double vision</li>\n<li>Generalised weakness</li>\n<li>Permanent loss of muscle tone with repeated injection</li>\n<li>Flu-like syndrome</li>\n<li>Development of antibodies to BOTOX<sup>&reg;</sup></li>\n<li>Infection (extremely rare)</li>\n<li>Unsatisfactory results</li>\n</ul>\n<p>BOTOX<sup>&reg;</sup> contains human-derived albumin and carries a theoretic risk of virus transmission. There have been no reports of disease transmission through BOTOX<sup>&reg;</sup>.&nbsp; If you are pregnant, nursing or are allergic to albumin (eggs), you should not receive injections. It is not known if Botox is harmful to the fetus, or if it is transmitted in breastmilk.</p>\n<p>The long term risks of Botox is unknown. Additional risk factors may be discovered over time.</p>\n<p>Botox is only FDA approved for glabellar lines and forehead lines. All other areas are &ldquo;off label&rdquo;.</p>\n<p>I understand the above and have had the risks, benefits and alternatives explained to me.&nbsp; I give my informed consent for BOTOX<sup>&reg;</sup>&nbsp;injections today. I accept the financial cost of the treatment today.</p>\n<p>&nbsp;<br />Patient Signature&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; _______________________</p>\n<p>Dr Murphy signature&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;________________________ &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp;&nbsp;</p>\n<p>Date ___________________</p>\n</td>\n<td style=\"text-align: left;\" width=\"301\">\n<p style=\"text-align: left;\"><strong><img src=\"https://crm.pabau.com/cdn/template_archive//template_attachments/d7afb5ad7f8db45c89c26543d909b798.png\" alt=\"\" width=\"85\" height=\"68\" />Dermal Filler Consent Form </strong></p>\n<p><strong>(Juv&eacute;derm/ Vycross, <sup>&reg;</sup> Belotero<sup>&reg;</sup>, Perfectha Radiesse,)</strong></p>\n<p>The first three dermal fillers are made of hyaluronic acid, a natural substance already found in the human body used to deliver nutrients and hydrate the skin by bonding with water.&nbsp; This gel is injected into facial tissue to smooth wrinkles and folds, especially around the mouth and nose.</p>\n<p>Juvederm is a Hyaluronic acid, which naturally occurs in the human body (a sugar). It hydrates the skin by holding in water. Vycross range is the top range of Juvederm injectable HA filler.</p>\n<p>Radiesse is&nbsp; tiny smooth calcium hydroxylapatite microspheres suspended in a sodium carboxymethylcellulose gel carrier. Upon injection it acts as a filler and then starts a process of neocollagenesis, stinulating the bodys own collagen, giving results for over a year. We use it for moderate to sever wrinkles or folds.</p>\n<p>&nbsp;<strong>Possible Side Effects:</strong></p>\n<ul>\n<li>Bleeding, redness, brusing, pain, allergic reaction</li>\n<li>Discoloration, lumpiness, irregularity, asymmetry, itching</li>\n<li>Infection, skin reaction (acne like), visible material (Tyndall effect)</li>\n<li>Damage to deeper structures/ vessel injection causing skin necrosis/ blindness (very rare)</li>\n<li>Over/ under correction/ unsatisfactory result</li>\n<li>Filler migration</li>\n<li>Skin necrosis</li>\n<li>Antibody to fillers</li>\n<li>Scarring</li>\n</ul>\n<p>I have read the information about hyaluronic acid and I have discussed the risks and benefits of dermal filler treatment with my practitioner. Additional costs may occur should complications arise from the injections, that will also be my responsibility.&nbsp; I accept and understand this.</p>\n<p>I accept full responsibility for the charges that this treatment incurs as outlined to me. I understand the information provided, and I agree to being treated with one of the hyaluronic acids/CaHA.</p>\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\n<p><br /><br />Patient&rsquo;s Signature&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; ______________________</p>\n<p>Dr Siun Murphy&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; ______________________&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; <br /><br />Date&nbsp;______________________ &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp;&nbsp;</p>\n</td>\n</tr>\n</tbody>\n</table>\n<table style=\"height: 458px;\" width=\"1016\">\n<tbody>\n<tr>\n<td width=\"529\">\n<p style=\"text-align: left;\"><span style=\"text-decoration: underline;\"><strong>Toxin:</strong></span><strong>&nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp;&nbsp;<span style=\"text-decoration: underline;\">Filler:</span></strong></p>\n<p><strong>&nbsp;<img src=\"https://crm.pabau.com/cdn/template_archive//template_attachments/222f804ec7eda650996c43b8089ac63c.png\" alt=\"\" width=\"161\" height=\"180\" />&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;</strong></p>\n<p style=\"text-align: left;\"><strong>&nbsp;<br /></strong><strong>Date: &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; </strong>&nbsp;____________________<strong> &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp;</strong></p>\n<p style=\"text-align: left;\"><strong>Consent: &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; </strong>&nbsp;_____________________</p>\n<p style=\"text-align: left;\"><strong>Signed: &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp;</strong>_____________________</p>\n<p style=\"text-align: left;\"><strong>Other Tx:</strong></p>\n</td>\n<td width=\"492\">\n<p style=\"text-align: left;\"><span style=\"text-decoration: underline;\"><strong>Toxin:</strong></span><strong>&nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp;&nbsp;<span style=\"text-decoration: underline;\">Filler:</span></strong></p>\n<p><strong>&nbsp;<img src=\"https://crm.pabau.com/cdn/template_archive//template_attach