<br />Reference: your name<br /><br /> To help us provide the best possible service it would be helpful if you could<span style=\"text-decoration: underline;\"> please&nbsp;</span><span style=\"text-decoration: underline;\">fill-out</span><span style=\"text-decoration: underline;\"> the attached form</span>&nbsp;above which should take no more than a few minutes to complete.&nbsp;<br />This will enable us to be aware of any previous treatments you have undertaken, medical history, allergies and any overall health care issues. Please be assured you data will be held in accordance with UK Medical Law.<br /><br /></p>\n<p><strong>Pre-treatment advice</strong></p>\n<ul>\n<li>We advise you to schedule our appointment 2 weeks prior to any special event to allow the treatment area to settle.</li>\n</ul>\n<ul>\n<li>We will not treat clients who are due to fly within 48hours of treatment.</li>\n</ul>\n<ul>\n<li>Please try and arrive with the area of treatment make up free.</li>\n</ul>\n<ul>\n<li>Avoid alcohol for 24 hours prior to your appointment.&nbsp;</li>\n</ul>\n<ul>\n<li>Please notify Youtopia Aesthetics as soon as possible if you develop a cold sore or rash the area we plan to treat, develop an illness or are on antibiotics as we may need to reschedule your appointment.</li>\n</ul>\n<ul>\n<li><strong>Avoid</strong> asprin and anti-inflammatory medication 48 hours prior to your treatment to help minimise bruising.</li>\n</ul>\n<ul>\n<li><strong>Do not</strong> stop any prescribed mediation prior to consulting your GP. We require you to complete a medical questionnaire prior to your booked appointment a link is contained within your confirmation email.</li>\n</ul>\n<ul>\n<li>Please be aware if you take anticoagulant mediation, high does omega 3 or vitamin E your likelihood of bleeding and bruising will be increased, please inform Youtopia Aesthetics prior to treatment.</li>\n</ul>\n<ul>\n<li>Under no circumstance will we treat any client who is pregnant or breast feeding.&nbsp;</li>\n</ul>\n<ul>\n<li>No treatment for under 18 year olds. If you&rsquo;re lucky enough to look under 18 please bring ID to your appointment.</li>\n</ul>\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\n<p>We look forward to treating you soon at one of our clinics, please see address details below. Any problems please email <a href=\"mailto:info@youtopiaaesthetics.co.uk\">info@youtopiaaesthetics.co.uk</a>&nbsp;or contact 07553238581.&nbsp;<br /><br /><strong>Cannock&nbsp;clinic:</strong> 88 Forge close, Cannock, Staffordshire, WS11 8JJ<br /><br /><strong>Stoke-on-Trent clinic:</strong> Hairology, 24 Goldenhill&nbsp;Road, Stoke-on-Trent ST4 3DW<br /><br /><strong>Ashbourne, Derby clinic:</strong> Viva Hair and Beauty, Shawcroft&nbsp;Centre, Ashbourne, DE6 1GD</p>\n</td>\n</tr>\n</tbody>\n</table>\n<!-- [if mso]>\n				</td>\n				<![endif]--> <!-- [if mso]>\n				</tr>\n				</table>\n				<![endif]--></td>\n</tr>\n</tbody>\n</table>\n</td>\n</tr>\n</tbody>\n</table>\n</td>\n</tr>\n<tr>\n<td align=\"right\" valign=\"top\"><img class=\"mcnImage\" style=\"display: block; max-width: 540px;\" src=\"https://gallery.mailchimp.com/27aac8a65e64c994c4416d6b8/images/leafshadowhorz.png\" alt=\"\" width=\"540\" height=\"15\" /></td>\n</tr>\n</tbody>\n</table>\n</td>\n</tr>\n</tbody>\n</table>\n<!-- // END BODY --></td>\n</tr>\n<tr>\n<td style=\"padding-bottom: 40px;\" align=\"center\" valign=\"top\"><!-- BEGIN FOOTER // -->\n<table id=\"templateFooter\" border=\"0\" width=\"100%\" cellspacing=\"0\" cellpadding=\"0\">\n<tbody>\n<tr>\n<td align=\"center\" valign=\"top\">\n<table class=\"templateContainer\" border=\"0\" width=\"640\" cellspacing=\"0\" cellpadding=\"0\">\n<tbody>\n<tr>\n<td align=\"right\" valign=\"top\">\n<table class=\"templateContainer\" border=\"0\" width=\"600\" cellspacing=\"0\" cellpadding=\"0\">\n<tbody>\n<tr>\n<td class=\"footerContainer\" style=\"padding-top: 10px; padding-bottom: 10px;\" valign=\"top\">\n<table class=\"mcnTextBlock\" style=\"min-width: 100%;\" border=\"0\" width=\"100%\" cellspacing=\"0\" cellpadding=\"0\">\n<tbody class=\"mcnTextBlockOuter\">\n<tr>\n<td class=\"mcnTextBlockInner\" style=\"padding-top: 9px;\" valign=\"top\"><!-- [if mso]>\n				<table align=\"left\" border=\"0\" cellspacing=\"0\" cellpadding=\"0\" width=\"100%\" style=\"width:100%;\">\n				<tr>\n				<![endif]--> <!-- [if mso]>\n				<td valign=\"top\" width=\"599\" style=\"width:599px;\">\n				<![endif]-->\n<table class=\"mcnTextContentContainer\" style=\"max-width: 100%; min-width: 100%;\" border=\"0\" width=\"100%\" cellspacing=\"0\" cellpadding=\"0\" align=\"left\">\n<tbody>\n<tr>\n<td class=\"mcnTextContent\" style=\"padding: 0 18px 9px 18px;\" valign=\"top\"><em>Update your preferences.</em></td>\n</tr>\n</tbody>\n</table>\n<!-- [if mso]>\n				</td>\n				<![endif]--> <!-- [if mso]>\n				</tr>\n				</table>\n				<![endif]--></td>\n</tr>\n</tbody>\n</table>\n</td>\n</tr>\n</tbody>\n</table>\n</td>\n</tr>\n</tbody>\n</table>\n</td>\n</tr>\n</tbody>\n</table>\n<!-- // END FOOTER --></td>\n</tr>\n</tbody>\n</table>\n<!-- // END TEMPLATE --></td>\n</tr>\n</tbody>\n</table>\n</center>\n</body>\n</html>', 0, 'email', '0000-00-00 00:00:00', '0000-00-00 00:00:00', 0, 0, 0, '', '', 0, 'confirmation', '', '', 0, 0),
                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                           (159163, 0, 'Refresh', 'Important Update regarding Dr Strawford', '<!DOCTYPE html>\n<html>\n<head>\n</head>\n<body>\n<div><img style=\"display: block; margin-left: auto; margin-right: auto;\" src=\"https://crm.pabau.com/cdn/template_archive/2723/template_attachments/6e7f3ef24e45d80b63fe6874d1718a59.JPG\" alt=\"\" /></div>\n<br /><br /><br /><br /><span style=\"font-size: 14px;\">Dear Patient</span><br /><br /><span style=\"font-size: 14px;\">Please accept our apologies for the confusion our previous email may have caused.&nbsp; I would just like to explain that it is only the Plymouth Clinic location that will be changing.&nbsp; Dr Strawford&nbsp;will continue to offer appointments and his extensive range of treatments&nbsp;in Bristol, Glastonbury,&nbsp;Dorchester&nbsp;and Plymouth.<br /><br /></span><br /><span style=\"font-size: 14px;\">If you are a patient and see Dr Strawford\'s&nbsp;in Plymouth we will be phoning you over the next few days to make sure you are aware of the change in location.&nbsp; If, however, you would like to discuss this beforehand please do not hesitate to call on 0800 298 2391 or email&nbsp;<a href=\"mailto:natalie@skinexcellenceclinics.co.uk\">natalie@skinexcellenceclinics.co.uk<br /></a></span>\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\n<p><span style=\"font-size: 14px;\"><strong>As previously advised the new address for Plymouth patients is:-&nbsp;</strong></span></p>\n<p><span style=\"font-size: 14px;\"><strong>Elburton Aesthetic Clinic</strong></span></p>\n<p><span style=\"font-size: 14px;\"><strong>49 Springfield Road</strong></span></p>\n<p><span style=\"font-size: 14px;\"><strong>Elburton</strong></span></p>\n<p><span style=\"font-size: 14px;\"><strong>Plymouth</strong></span></p>\n<p><span style=\"font-size: 14px;\"><strong>PL9 8EP</strong></span></p>\n<p><span style=\"font-size: 14px;\">Please note that all telephone calls and bookings for Plymouth are to be made directly to Dr Strawford&rsquo;s PA &ndash; Natalie Tandy on <strong>0800 298 2391</strong>.&nbsp; This is Natalie&rsquo;s direct number and all calls will be answered between 9am and 6pm.&nbsp; Please note that 0800 number is free from all mobiles and landlines.&nbsp; Alternatively, please feel free to email Natalie at <a href=\"mailto:natalie@skinexcellenceclinics.co.uk\">natalie@skinexcellenceclinics.co.uk</a>.</span></p>\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\n<p><span style=\"font-size: 14px;\">We look forward to seeing you all shortly.&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;</span></p>\n<p><span style=\"font-size: 14px;\">Kind regards</span><br /><br /><br /><br />Natalie Tandy<br />Clinic Manager<br />Skin Excellence Clinics</p>\n</body>\n</html>', 0, 'email', '2018-04-10 08:14:57', '0000-00-00 00:00:00', 0, 0, 0, '', '', 0, 'general', '', '', 0, 0),
                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                           (161569, 0, 'Waxing Aftercare', 'Waxing Aftercare Advice', '<!DOCTYPE html>\n<html>\n<head>\n</head>\n<body>\n<div style=\"text-align: center;\">[COMPANYLOGO]<br /><br /><span style=\"font-size: 16px;\"><strong>Thank you for your recent visit to&nbsp;[COMPANYNAME]</strong></span><br /><br /><br /><span style=\"font-size: 14px;\">Following your Waxing treatment with us we would like to advise you of the recommended&nbsp;aftercare to optimise the results of your treatment;</span><br /><br /><span style=\"font-size: 14px;\">Following a waxing treatment it is normal to experience erythema&nbsp;(redness) and slight soreness, if these symptoms persist please call us.</span><br /><br /><span style=\"font-size: 14px;\">We recommend that you keep the waxed area clean and avoid friction for the next 24-48 hours.</span><br /><br /><span style=\"font-size: 14px;\">Avoid direct heat to the area, including sauna, steam room, jacuzzi\'s&nbsp;for the next 24-48 hours</span><br /><br /><span style=\"font-size: 14px;\">Avoid exposure to UV Light for the next 24-48 hours.&nbsp;</span><br /><br /><span style=\"font-size: 14px;\">Do not have any massage treatment for the next 24-48 hours.&nbsp;</span><br /><br /><span style=\"font-size: 14px;\">Fake Tan should not be applied to the area immediately after tanning.</span><br /><br /><span style=\"font-size: 14px;\">No swimming for the next 24-48 hours.</span><br /><br /><span style=\"font-size: 14px;\">Deodorant or anything perfumed should not be applied to the area that has been waxed for 24-48 hours as this could make the area very sore</span><br /><br /><span style=\"font-size: 14px;\">Make-up should be avoided following facial hair removal for that day although mineral make up is fine.</span><br /><br /><span style=\"font-size: 14px;\">Tight clothing should be avoided following any waxing treatment for 24-48 hours as this can aggravate the area that&rsquo;s been waxed.</span><br /><br /><span style=\"font-size: 14px;\">Waxing removes dead skin so the skin may be a little lighter immediately following treatment but colour will return to normal within a few hours.</span><br /><br /><span style=\"font-size: 14px;\">Dry brush the area that has been waxed a couple of times a week.&nbsp;Get a brush that you would scrub your back with made from wood and bristle.&nbsp;Just before you step into the bath or shower, take the dry brush and brush your skin whilst it&rsquo;s dry. </span><br /><br /><span style=\"font-size: 14px;\">A heat reaction may be seen on the skin for several hours following treatment and this is quite normal.&nbsp;This will vary from a mild redness to a much stronger skin reaction and some people have red dots on the waxed area for several hours. </span><br /><br /><span style=\"font-size: 14px;\">If any spots or rashes persist for more than a week, or become infected, Please consult with&nbsp;your GP.</span><br /><br /><span style=\"font-size: 14px;\">If the aftercare advice given&nbsp;is followed the skin will return to normal within 24 hours. If the reaction is still present after this time or worsens, it may be that you have had an allergic reaction to the wax, and you should seek medical advice from your GP.&nbsp;</span><br /><br />\n<h2>Preventing ingrown hairs</h2>\n<p><span style=\"font-size: 14px;\">In grown hairs occur when a new hair can\'t break through the surface of the skin and curls back into the pore instead, often resulting in a spot. Shaving and waxing can often exacerbate the situation, but&nbsp; there are things that you can do.</span></p>\n<p><span style=\"font-size: 14px;\">Starting a few days after your appointment, gently dry brush the skin 2 or 3 times a week or&nbsp;use a gentle exfoliator. Using an antibacterial body wash will also help.&nbsp;Moisturise the area every day, which will keep the skin supple and help new hairs to break through.&nbsp;</span></p>\n<h2><span style=\"font-size: 14px;\">Other information</span></h2>\n<p><span style=\"font-size: 14px;\">You may notice a small amount of regrowth after a week or so.&nbsp; It can take upto 4 treatments for your hair to get on a growth cycle thats gives best results. Hair needs to be at least 1/2cm long before it can be successfully removed by waxing.</span></p>\n<p><span style=\"font-size: 14px;\">Please do not shave between your appointments.</span></p>\n<p><span style=\"font-size: 14px;\">To maintain your smooth appearence, I would recommend regular&nbsp;waxing every 4-6 weeks.</span></p>\n<span style=\"font-size: 14px;\">To re-book click below;<br /></span>[COMPANYWEBSITE]<br /><br /><br /></div>\n</body>\n</html>', 0, 'email', '0000-00-00 00:00:00', '0000-00-00 00:00:00', 0, 0, 0, '', '', 0, 'aftercare', '', '', 0, 0),
                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                           (165301, 0, 'LVR enquiry ', 'Thank you for your enquiry ', '<!DOCTYPE html>\n<html>\n<head>\n</head>\n<body>\n<em><em><strong><span style=\"color: #3eb589;\"><img src=\"https://crm.pabau.com/cdn/template_archive/4065/template_attachments/071249ff91531c25053c5c38aebd299a.jpg\" alt=\"\" /><br /><span style=\"font-size: 14px;\"><span style=\"color: #000000;\">Dear&nbsp;[APPOINTMENTFIRSTNAME],</span></span><br /><br />&nbsp;</span></strong></em></em>\n<p><span style=\"font-size: 14px;\">Thank you for your enquiry to Premier Laser &amp; Skin.</span></p>\n<p><span style=\"font-size: 14px;\">As a warm welcome we are offering you &pound;25 towards your treatment package with us, if you book your free consultation today.&nbsp;Bring this email with you to your consultation to receive&nbsp;your &pound;25.&nbsp;</span><br /><br /></p>\n<p><span style=\"font-size: 14px;\">The best way forward is to book you in for a no obligation, complimentary consultation with one of our specialists who will&nbsp;advise you in depth on the laser tattoo removal treatment.&nbsp;During the&nbsp;consultation, your specialist will go through an in depth treatment plan, show you before and after photos&nbsp;so you can get an idea of results to expect, conduct a patch test if needed and&nbsp;answer any questions you may have.<br /><br />Laser removal is suitable for thread or spider veins (those that are 3mm and less in diameter). Our laser vein removal procedure targets and cauterises the veins, effectively cutting off the blood supply without damage to the epidermis or surrounding tissue.&nbsp;Please note; we will not treat veins on the nose or ankle area. Treating veins in these areas have common side effects that pose greater risks, indentation on the nose and blood clotting&nbsp;in the ankles are some of them. Due to the wavelength needed for this type of removal, we can only treat skin types 1-3. If you have questions, feel free to call us on 02038718218.&nbsp;<br /><br />&nbsp;</span></p>\n<p><span style=\"font-size: 14px;\">All of our clinics are open Monday - Friday 10am - 8pm, Saturday 10am - 6pm.&nbsp;</span><br /><span style=\"font-size: 14px;\">Kingston,&nbsp;Clapham,&nbsp;Notting&nbsp;Hill and&nbsp;Fulham&nbsp;are open on Sunday 10am-5pm.&nbsp;</span></p>\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\n<p><span style=\"font-size: 14px;\">Should you require any further information do not hesitate to contact us on 0203 871 8218&nbsp;or email hello@premierlaserclinic.co.uk.</span></p>\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\n<p><br /><em><strong><span style=\"font-size: 14px;\">Kind regards,<br /><br />[YOURNAME]<br /><br />Premier Laser &amp; Skin Treatment advisor</span></strong></em></p>\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\n<p><br /><br /></p>\n</body>\n</html>', 0, 'email', '2018-06-06 14:10:30', '0000-00-00 00:00:00', 0, 0, 0, '', '', 0, 'leads', '', '', 0, 0),
