                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                           (215112, 0, 'initial Ortho Enquiry ', 'Ten Dental+Facial Orthodontic enquiry', '<!DOCTYPE html>\n<html>\n<head>\n</head>\n<body>\n<div style=\"text-align: center;\"><img src=\"my computer\" alt=\"\" /><img src=\"https://crm.pabau.com/cdn/template_archive//template_attachments/75d9dc042f86c607cd7dd2a7bebc3eed.png\" alt=\"\" /><br /><br /><br /><br /></div>\n<div style=\"text-align: left;\">\n<p>Good Afternoon ,</p>\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\n<p>Thank you for your enquiry.</p>\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\n<p>At our award-winning practices, we can offer you a free orthodontic consultation with one of our Treatment Coordinators (TCO). They are qualified Dental Nurses who will be able to discuss:</p>\n<ol>\n<li>The different types of Treatments we offer (showing cases, modules and what your treatment journey would look like)</li>\n<li>The benefits of each type of appliance</li>\n<li>The cost of treatment - Our TCO&rsquo;s will assess your teeth, as well as taking photos of your teeth and give you a number of options. If you are interested in having any form of orthodontic treatment you will be able to sit with an orthodontist for a free consultation.</li>\n<li>The different payment plans that we offer.</li>\n<li>If you bring the quotes that you have been issued already the TCO will be able to go over this with you</li>\n</ol>\n<p>If you would like me to go ahead and book you a consultation please let me know which location works best for you and any dates and times you are available. We can offer this free consultation in our&nbsp;Balham&nbsp;or Clapham&nbsp;High Street practices.<br /><br />Please do not hesitate to contact me at this address or call me on 0208 396 4069 should you have any questions, I have attached the following links for your reference.<br /><br />The following link will show you a number of case studies - <a href=\"https://www.tendental.com/smile-gallery/\">https://www.tendental.com/smile-gallery/</a></p>\n<p>Enjoy your day, and please let me know what day and time are best for you to book your free consultation.<br /><br />Kind regards,&nbsp;<br /><br />Craig<br /><strong>Customer Relationship &amp; Data Manager</strong>&nbsp;</p>\n</div>\n</body>\n</html>', 0, 'email', '2019-01-24 10:17:03', '0000-00-00 00:00:00', 0, 0, 0, '', '', 0, 'general', '', '', 0, 0),
                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                           (215799, 0, 'Patient Guide to Filler', 'Patient Guide to Filler', '<!DOCTYPE html>\n<html>\n<head>\n</head>\n<body>\n<br />&nbsp;Dear&nbsp;[APPOINTMENTNAME],<br /><br /><br />Please find attached the guide to Filler.<br /><br /><br />&nbsp;Yours,&nbsp;[COMPANYNAME]\n</body>\n</html>', 0, 'email', '2019-02-06 09:26:40', '0000-00-00 00:00:00', 0, 0, 0, '', '', 0, 'aftercare', '', '', 0, 1),
                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                           (217226, 0, 'Appointment Confirmation', 'Confirmation of your Appointment', '<!DOCTYPE html>\n<html>\n<head>\n</head>\n<body>\n<a href=\"https://www.meyerclinic.co.uk\"><img src=\"https://crm.pabau.com/cdn/template_archive/7876/template_attachments/e354d677f9f6e5008c066468ba8a0dc5.png\" alt=\"\" /></a><br /><br /><br />Thank you for booking with Meyer Clinic<br /><br />Dear&nbsp;[APPOINTMENTFIRSTNAME]<br /><br />We look forward to seeing you on&nbsp;[ADATE] at&nbsp;[ASTARTTIME]<br /><br />Due to the current situation with Covid-19, we do require all patients to complete and return a consent form ahead of their appointment, which is attached. You may email it back to <a href=\"mailto:info@meyerclinic.co.uk\">info@meyerclinic.co.uk</a>&nbsp;or bring it with you to your appointment.<br /><br /><br />Please rest assured that when you come&nbsp;for your appointment, we will be operating within government guidelines, with strict measures in place to prevent the spread of Coronavirus. These protocols will be in place to keep you and our team safe.&nbsp;&nbsp;<br /><br />\n<ul>\n<li>We are staggering our appointments to reduce the number of patients at the clinic at any one time.</li>\n<li>When you first arrive for your appointment, please come in to the reception area, where a member of our staff will check you in.</li>\n<li>We would ask&nbsp;you to please observe the strict 2metres social distancing measure and use the provided hand sanitiser.</li>\n<li>We will then ask you to return to your car and drive around to the car park at the rear of the building. When we are ready for you, we will come out to collect you.</li>\n<li>You will be asked to sanitise your hands again and be given a pair of protective&nbsp;gloves and a mask. All members of our team will be wearing PPE.</li>\n<li>After your appointment, we will escort you out of the building, back to your vehicle.</li>\n<li>After each&nbsp;appointment, we will be cleaning down our surgeries which may result in a longer wait time for your appointment. Please be&nbsp;patient with us.</li>\n</ul>\n<br />If you are suffering with any of the following symptoms, we would ask you to contact us in advance so that we can re-schedule&nbsp;your appointment.<br /><br />\n<ul>\n<li>Fever</li>\n<li>Shortness of Breath</li>\n<li>Loss of Sense of Taste or Smell</li>\n<li>Dry Cough</li>\n<li>Runny Nose</li>\n<li>Sore Throat</li>\n</ul>\n<br />If you do need to cancel or reschedule&nbsp;your appointment please allow a minimum of 24hrs notice as you may be subject to a cancellation charge.<br /><br />Please note, during these challenging times our restrooms will not be open to our patients.&nbsp;<br /><br />We look forward to seeing you back in clinic and will do our utmost&nbsp;to keep you safe.<br /><br />Best wishes<br /><br />Meyer Clinic<br />Main Road, Fishbourne, West Sussex&nbsp; PO18 8AN<br />01243 771455<br /><a href=\"mailto:info@meyerclinic.co.uk\">info@meyerclinic.co.uk</a><a href=\"mailto:info@meyerclinic.co.uk\"><br /><br /></a><a href=\"https://www.meyerclinic.co.uk\">www.meyerclinic.co.uk</a><br /><br />\n</body>\n</html>', 0, 'email', '2019-02-28 16:42:44', '0000-00-00 00:00:00', 0, 0, 0, '', '', 0, 'confirmation', '', '', 0, 1),
                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                           (217429, 0, 'Botox Aftercare ', 'Post-treatment', '<!DOCTYPE html>\n<html>\n<head>\n</head>\n<body>\n<li></li>\n<br /><span style=\"font-size: 12px;\"><span style=\"text-decoration: underline;\"><strong>Anti-Wrinkle Injection<br /><br /></strong></span>Botulinum toxin is a prescription muscle relaxant medicine and is used to treat several conditions within the body. It contains the active substance Botulinum&nbsp;Toxin A. It works by partially blocking nerve impulses and the effect depends upon where it is injected.</span><br /><span style=\"font-size: 12px;\">If injected into a muscle it will reduce excessive contractions of that muscle. It can be used for the temporary improvement in the appearance of vertical lines between the eyebrows (Glabella) seen at maximum frown (Frontails) and fan-shaped lines from the corner of the eyes (Crows feet) at maximum smile.</span><br /><br /><br /><span style=\"text-decoration: underline;\"><strong>Possible Risks, Complications &amp; Side Effects to Botox<br /><br /></strong></span>\n<ul>\n<li>Bruising/swelling/skin redness</li>\n<li>Stinging/burning</li>\n<li>Headaches</li>\n<li>Infection at treatment site</li>\n<li>Asymmetry of facial expressions</li>\n<li>Drooping of the eyelid or eyebrow (ptosis)/ double vision, dry eyes</li>\n<li>Hypersensitivity, Allergic response, Anaphylactic reaction (rare but can occur)</li>\n</ul>\n<br /><br /><span style=\"text-decoration: underline;\"><strong>General Aftercare Post treatment with Botulinum&nbsp;Toxin<br /><br /></strong></span>\n<ul>\n<li>You may find it helpful to apply cold gauze to the treated area</li>\n<li>Treatment normally takes 3-7 days to start to take effect. 10-14 days to reach full effect</li>\n<li>Do not rub, touch, apply make-up the areas for at least 4 hours after treatment</li>\n<li>Avoid extreme heat/cold fo up to 1-week post treatment - no saunas</li>\n<li>Abstain from Alcohol, heavy exercise for 24 hours</li>\n<li>Stay upright for 4 hours</li>\n<li>Stay out of Sunlight/UV radiation until redness and swelling has resolved</li>\n<li>Botulinum&nbsp;treatment lasts for around 3 - 6 months depending on metabolism &amp; lifestyle</li>\n</ul>\n<br /><span style=\"text-decoration: underline;\"><strong><br /><br /><br /><br /></strong></span><br /><span style=\"text-decoration: underline;\"><strong><br /><br /></strong></span>\n</body>\n</html>', 0, 'email', '2019-03-08 13:32:15', '0000-00-00 00:00:00', 0, 0, 0, '', '', 0, 'aftercare', '', '', 0, 1);
