                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                           (220997, 0, 'Botox Aftercare', 'Your Botox Aftercare', '<!DOCTYPE html>\n<html>\n<head>\n</head>\n<body>\n<h2 style=\"text-align: center;\"><span style=\"text-decoration: underline;\"><strong>Wrinkle Relaxation Post Treatment Advice</strong></span></h2>\n<div><strong>&nbsp;</strong></div>\n<h3><span style=\"text-decoration: underline;\"><strong>After Treatment</strong></span></h3>\n<div>&nbsp;</div>\n<div>After treatment it is expected that you will start to see an improvement within 5 to 10 days. For some people this takes longer. The full result may be judged at 2-3 weeks. You may be invited to attend a review appointment at 2-3 weeks where the success of the treatment may be assessed and adjustments to your personal treatment plan made, if necessary.</div>\n<div>&nbsp;</div>\n<div>Small red spots on the skin usually disappear in a few hours. Transient stinging of the skin is normal after injection&nbsp;(10-15&nbsp;minutes). If bruising is to occur, it is usually is apparent at day&nbsp;2-3&nbsp;and will typically resolve over&nbsp;5-10 days, although this is rare. You will not see any effect for around 5 days and the full effect is visible at around 2-3 weeks.</div>\n<div>&nbsp;</div>\n<div>Should you experience any unexpected side effects or any that concern you, please contact the clinic on [COMPANYPHONE] as soon as possible.</div>\n<div>&nbsp;<br /><br /></div>\n<h3><span style=\"text-decoration: underline;\"><strong>What to do after treatment</strong></span></h3>\n<div><strong>&nbsp;</strong></div>\n<div>\n<ul>\n<li>Drink plenty of fluids but avoid hot drinks</li>\n<li>Please do not wear your normal make up for 12 hours with the exception of Oxygenetix, Exuviance or other post surgical make up</li>\n<li>In the evening of the treatment you may gently wash your face and use your regular wash and lotions</li>\n<li>You may gently apply a cool compress to any red or swollen areas for the first 48 hours to help decrease the swelling more quickly. No pressure is to be exerted onto the face. The compress should only be gently placed on the treated areas</li>\n<li>Remain upright either sitting or standing for at least 6 hours after treatment to avoid uneven distribution of product. Do not sleep with pressure on the face</li>\n<li>You may commence bathing the day after the procedure</li>\n<li>Wash your face very carefully, applying no pressure to the skin for 2 days</li>\n<li>You may require further treatment to obtain the desired results. You may be offered a follow up appointment for 4 weeks after your initial procedure</li>\n<li>If you are a smoker it may be recommended that you take vitamin c prior to the procedure to assist with healing.</li>\n<li>You may require further injections to obtain the desired results. You may be offered a follow up appointment for 2 weeks after your initial procedure. Any more than 4 weeks after the date of the procedure is not covered by the review appointment process if you have paid on a &ldquo;per area&rdquo; basis. Those undergoing treatment on a &ldquo;per unit&rdquo; basis will incur an additional charge should adjustments be made</li>\n</ul>\n</div>\n<div><strong>&nbsp;</strong></div>\n<h3><span style=\"text-decoration: underline;\"><strong>What NOT to do after treatment</strong></span></h3>\n<div>&nbsp;</div>\n<div>\n<ul>\n<li>Do not massage the area treated for the first 2 days following treatment. No facials, waxing or massage for the first 2 weeks</li>\n<li>Do not take aspirin, ibuprofen or other anti inflammatory medication for 24 hours after treatment as this may increase bruising. You may take paracetamol or codeine if you are uncomfortable</li>\n<li>Do not consume alcohol for 24 hours after receiving treatment</li>\n<li>No strenuous exercise or gardening for at least 24 days but light exercise such as walking is ok</li>\n<li>Do not have a sauna, hot tub or go in a tanning booth for 2 weeks after treatment. Always wear a broad spectrum, high factor sun protection (SPF 30-50) on the face, neck, d&eacute;colletage and hands</li>\n</ul>\n</div>\n<div>&nbsp;</div>\n<h3><span style=\"text-decoration: underline;\"><strong>What to watch out for after treatment</strong></span></h3>\n<div>&nbsp;</div>\n<div>\n<ul>\n<li>You may experience a &ldquo;heaviness&rdquo; of the brow, or a different way of your eyelid folding as the muscles settle into the new position. This typically resolves within 2 weeks. True drooping of the eyelid/brow is rare</li>\n<li>In some cases it may be necessary to add dermal filler to the forehead or temple to get the best results This additional treatment will be discussed with you at your consultation but is usually due to excessively deep lines or asymmetries in the skull. Costs are not covered by your initial procedure and are dependent on the degree or correction necessary</li>\n</ul>\n</div>\n<div>&nbsp;</div>\n<div><strong><strong>Please ensure you discuss your overall treatment programme with your doctor as this will enable you to receive the best results from treatment.&nbsp;We also offer dermal fillers, facial contouring, lip shaping and thread lifts. Please contact us for further information.<br /><br /><br /></strong></strong>\n<table style=\"height: 396px;\" border=\"0\" width=\"638\" cellspacing=\"0\" cellpadding=\"0\">\n<tbody>\n<tr>\n<td valign=\"top\"><br /><br /><br /><br /><br />[<img src=\"https://crm.pabau.com/cdn/template_archive//template_attachments/8a780023341210c120cc840ae09eb2d9.jpg\" alt=\"\" />]</td>\n<td>\n<table border=\"0\" cellspacing=\"0\" cellpadding=\"0\">\n<tbody>\n<tr>\n<td colspan=\"2\">[Brockweir&nbsp;Clinic Ltd</td>\n</tr>\n<tr>\n<td valign=\"top\" width=\"20\">p:</td>\n<td valign=\"top\">07429815753</td>\n</tr>\n<tr>\n<td valign=\"top\" width=\"20\">a:</td>\n<td valign=\"top\">Brockweir, Newport Road</td>\n</tr>\n<tr>\n<td valign=\"top\" width=\"20\">&nbsp;</td>\n<td valign=\"top\">Llantarnam,<br />Np44 3AE<br /><br /></td>\n</tr>\n<tr>\n<td valign=\"top\" width=\"20\">e:</td>\n<td valign=\"top\">Drtahsin.brockweirclinic@gmail.com<a href=\"mailto:hello@thelovelyclinic.co.uk\"><br /><br /></a></td>\n</tr>\n<tr>\n<td colspan=\"2\"><a href=\"https://www.facebook.com/TheLovelyClinic/\"><img src=\"http://cdn2.hubspot.net/hubfs/184235/dev_images/signature_app/facebook_sig.png\" alt=\"\" width=\"25\" height=\"25\" /></a>&nbsp;&nbsp;<a href=\"https://twitter.com/thelovelyclinic\"><img src=\"http://cdn2.hubspot.net/hubfs/184235/dev_images/signature_app/twitter_sig.png\" alt=\"\" width=\"25\" height=\"25\" /></a>&nbsp;&nbsp;<a href=\"https://www.instagram.com/thelovelyclinic/?hl=en\"><img src=\"http://cdn2.hubspot.net/hubfs/184235/dev_images/signature_app/instagram_sig.png\" alt=\"\" width=\"25\" height=\"25\" /></a></td>\n</tr>\n</tbody>\n</table>\n</td>\n</tr>\n</tbody>\n</table>\n<strong><br /><br /><br /><br /></strong></div>\n</body>\n</html>', 0, 'email', '0000-00-00 00:00:00', '0000-00-00 00:00:00', 0, 0, 0, '', '', 0, 'aftercare', '', '', 0, 0),
