                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                           (228432, 0, 'MAILS - Coolsculpting - Info', '', '<!DOCTYPE html>\n<html>\n<head>\n</head>\n<body>\n<p>Dear [LEADFNAME],<br /><br /></p>\n<p>We have received your email, <br /><br />Thank you for the trust you place in our clinic. In response to your request, please read the following: <br /><br />Cryolipolysis can reduce localized fat deposits up to 30 to 45% at each session. For some patients, a single treatment is enough to achieve their goal. Others choose to have additional sessions to lose even more fat mass.<br /> <br />Please note that the results are not immediate. They are visible after two months and optimal after four months. It\'s the time required for the fat released by the adipocytes damaged by the cold to be slowly and naturally eliminated by the lymphatic system and absorbed by the liver.<br /><br />However, the body will continue to get rid of fat cells for up to four to six months after the treatment.<br /><br />In addition to slimming, the action of the cold also leads to a tightening of the skin and an improvement in cellulite.<br /><br />Cryolipolysis treats small excess fat located on the hips, stomach, inner thighs, saddlebags, buttocks, arms and back. Under no circumstances can it replace a diet, if one is necessary.<br /><br />A session lasts between one and four hours depending on the number of areas treated.<br /><br />The doctor places a gel pad to protect the skin and then applies the device combining the effects of suction and cold to the area to be treated. When the device pulls the rolls into the cooling panels, the patient feels a strong pinch and intense cold. Tingling may also occur but disappears as the treated area becomes numb.<br /><br />Within a few minutes, the temperature, which is continuously controlled by the device, dropped to 14F.<br /><br />The cooling treatment leads to the natural death of the targeted fat cells. The surrounding cells and muscles are less sensitive to the cold and are not affected. Over the next few weeks, the body begins to eliminate the dead fat cells on its own.<br /><br />During the first few minutes of cooling, you may feel pressure and intense cold. This feeling disappears fairly quickly. Sitting comfortably, you can read, listen to music, check your e-mails or take a nap during the treatment.<br /><br />The resumption of activities is immediate. The treated area is red and slightly numb for a few hours. Sometimes, due to the suction required to pinch the skin to be treated, some bruising may occur depending on the sensitivity of the skin, but it disappears after a few days. Some patients experience aches and pains for 7 to 10 days.</p>\n<p>I would also like to draw your attention to the many copies of this device out there in the market.<br /><br />Today, many companies in Asia and Europe have started to mimic the cryolipolysis technique. However, these low-cost devices can be dangerous. At best they act at a way too high temperature and are inefficient. At worst, they burn the skin because they do not have the technology to control the impact of cold on the skin.<br /><br />This is why we insist on not confusing Cryolypolise, a generic word increasingly used, with CoolSculpting&reg; founded by Zeltiq.<br /><br />As it is difficult to provide you with all the information by e-mail, I advise you to book a consultation appointment with one of our specialists in this technique.<br /><br />I hope that I have answered all your questions, and remain at your disposal if you have any further questions or if you would like to schedule an appointment with one of our specialists.<br /><br />You can also contact me directly at 212 812 1107.<br /><br />I look forward to meeting you very soon,<br /><br /> Sincerely,<br /><br /></p>\n<table border=\"0\" cellspacing=\"0\" cellpadding=\"0\">\n<tbody>\n<tr>\n<td style=\"font-family: Calibri, Arial; color: #424242; font-size: 10pt; padding-bottom: 10px;\"><strong><span style=\"font-size: 12pt;\"><em>[STAFFIRSTNAME]</em></span><br /><br /></strong><span style=\"font-size: 13pt;\"><strong>Clinique des Champs-Elys&eacute;es</strong></span>&nbsp;<br /><strong><span style=\"color: #293786;\">T&eacute;l.</span></strong> : 01 53 77&nbsp;25&nbsp;88 | <strong><span style=\"color: #293786;\">T&eacute;l2.</span></strong> : 01 53 77 26&nbsp;00</td>\n</tr>\n</tbody>\n</table>\n<table style=\"border-top: 1px solid #293786;\" border=\"0\" cellspacing=\"0\" cellpadding=\"0\">\n<tbody>\n<tr>\n<td height=\"80\"><img style=\"display: block;\" src=\"https://www.crpce.com/emailing/logo-signature2.png\" alt=\"Clinique des Champs-Elys&eacute;es\" width=\"263\" height=\"80\" border=\"0\" /></td>\n</tr>\n<tr>\n<td style=\"font-family: Calibri, Arial; color: #293786; font-size: 10pt; text-align: center;\" align=\"center\">61 av Franklin D.Roosevelt 75008 PARIS</td>\n</tr>\n<tr>\n<td align=\"center\">\n<table border=\"0\" cellspacing=\"0\" cellpadding=\"0\">\n<tbody>\n<tr>\n<td style=\"font-family: Calibri, Arial; color: #293786; font-size: 10pt;\" valign=\"middle\" bgcolor=\"#ffffff\" height=\"25\"><a style=\"color: #293786;\" title=\"www.crpce.com\" href=\"https://www.crpce.com/\">www.crpce.com</a> |</td>\n<td style=\"font-family: Calibri, Arial; color: #293786; font-size: 10pt;\" valign=\"middle\" bgcolor=\"#ffffff\" height=\"25\"><a title=\"Facebook\" href=\"https://www.facebook.com/crpce\"><img style=\"display: block;\" src=\"https://www.crpce.com/emailing/logo-fb.png\" alt=\"Facebook\" width=\"22\" height=\"15\" border=\"0\" /></a></td>\n<td style=\"font-family: Calibri, Arial; color: #293786; font-size: 10pt;\" valign=\"middle\" bgcolor=\"#ffffff\" height=\"25\"><a title=\"Twitter\" href=\"https://twitter.com/ccelysees\"><img style=\"display: block;\" src=\"https://www.crpce.com/emailing/logo-tw.png\" alt=\"Twitter\" width=\"22\" height=\"15\" border=\"0\" /></a></td>\n<td style=\"font-family: Calibri, Arial; color: #293786; font-size: 10pt;\" valign=\"middle\" bgcolor=\"#ffffff\" height=\"25\"><a title=\"Instagram\" href=\"https://www.instagram.com/clinique_des_champs_elysees\"><img style=\"display: block;\" src=\"https://www.crpce.com/emailing/logo-inst.png\" alt=\"Instagram\" width=\"22\" height=\"15\" border=\"0\" /></a></td>\n<td style=\"font-family: Calibri, Arial; color: #293786; font-size: 10pt;\" valign=\"middle\" bgcolor=\"#ffffff\" height=\"25\"><a title=\"You Tube\" href=\"https://www.youtube.com/user/CRPCE01\"><img style=\"display: block;\" src=\"https://www.crpce.com/emailing/logo-yt.png\" alt=\"You Tube\" width=\"22\" height=\"15\" border=\"0\" /></a></td>\n</tr>\n</tbody>\n</table>\n</td>\n</tr>\n</tbody>\n</table>\n</body>\n</html>', 0, 'email', '0000-00-00 00:00:00', '0000-00-00 00:00:00', 0, 0, 0, '', '', 0, 'general', '', '', 0, 1),
