]<br />[RESCHEDULE_TO_DATE_TIME]<br />Thank you for booking with [COMPANYNAME]<br />[APPOINTMENTFIRSTNAME]<br />[APPOINTMENTLASTNAME]<br />[APPOINTMENTNAME]<br /><br />[CUSTOM_CITY]<br />[CUSTOM_SPEC]<br /><br /><br />To help us provide the best possible service it would be helpful if you could<span style=\"text-decoration: underline;\">&nbsp;please&nbsp;</span><span style=\"text-decoration: underline;\">fill-out</span><span style=\"text-decoration: underline;\">&nbsp;the attached form</span>&nbsp;above which should take no more than a few minutes to complete.&nbsp;<br /><br />This will enable us to be aware of any previous treatments you have undertaken, medical history, allergies and any overall health care issues.</p>\n<p>Please be assured you data will be held in accordance with UK Medical Law.</p>\n<p>&nbsp;<a href=\" [CLIENT_PREFERENCES] \">Update your preferences<br /><br />D</a>ont&nbsp;mind this text below<br /><br />[CUSTOM.PickYourOwnAdventure]</p>\n</td>\n</tr>\n</tbody>\n</table>\n</td>\n</tr>\n</tbody>\n</table>\n</td>\n</tr>\n</tbody>\n</table>\n</td>\n</tr>\n<tr>\n<td align=\"right\" valign=\"top\"><img class=\"mcnImage\" style=\"display: block; max-width: 540px;\" src=\"https://gallery.mailchimp.com/27aac8a65e64c994c4416d6b8/images/leafshadowhorz.png\" alt=\"\" width=\"540\" height=\"15\" /></td>\n</tr>\n</tbody>\n</table>\n</td>\n</tr>\n</tbody>\n</table>\n</td>\n</tr>\n<tr>\n<td style=\"padding-bottom: 40px;\" align=\"center\" valign=\"top\">\n<table id=\"templateFooter\" border=\"0\" width=\"100%\" cellspacing=\"0\" cellpadding=\"0\">\n<tbody>\n<tr>\n<td align=\"center\" valign=\"top\">\n<table class=\"templateContainer\" border=\"0\" width=\"640\" cellspacing=\"0\" cellpadding=\"0\">\n<tbody>\n<tr>\n<td align=\"right\" valign=\"top\">\n<table class=\"templateContainer\" border=\"0\" width=\"600\" cellspacing=\"0\" cellpadding=\"0\">\n<tbody>\n<tr>\n<td class=\"footerContainer\" style=\"padding-top: 10px; padding-bottom: 10px;\" valign=\"top\">\n<table class=\"mcnTextBlock\" style=\"min-width: 100%;\" border=\"0\" width=\"100%\" cellspacing=\"0\" cellpadding=\"0\">\n<tbody class=\"mcnTextBlockOuter\">\n<tr>\n<td class=\"mcnTextBlockInner\" style=\"padding-top: 9px; text-align: center;\" valign=\"top\"><a href=\"[CLIENT_PREFERENCES]\">Update your preferences.</a></td>\n</tr>\n</tbody>\n</table>\n</td>\n</tr>\n</tbody>\n</table>\n</td>\n</tr>\n</tbody>\n</table>\n</td>\n</tr>\n</tbody>\n</table>\n</td>\n</tr>\n</tbody>\n</table>\n</td>\n</tr>\n</tbody>\n</table>\n</body>\\n</html>', 0, 'email', '2020-01-14 13:41:02', '0000-00-00 00:00:00', 0, 0, 0, '', '', 0, 'confirmation', '', '', 0, 1),
                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                           (230669, 0, 'AHI Post Op Instructions', '', '<!DOCTYPE html>\n<html>\n<head>\n</head>\n<body>\n<p><strong><img src=\"https://crm.pabau.com/cdn/template_archive/8435/template_attachments/a6b7ab452aafd3a279d57bd542346bf2.PNG\" alt=\"\" width=\"176\" height=\"73\" />&nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp;</strong></p>\n<p>&nbsp;<br /><span style=\"font-size: 14px;\"><strong>Advance Hair Implants Limited</strong></span></p>\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\n<p><span style=\"font-size: 14px;\"><strong>HOW TO CARE FOR YOUR TRANSPLANTED HAIR GRAFTS&nbsp;</strong></span><br /> </p>\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\n<p><span style=\"font-size: 14px;\">You have invested time and money in your grafts. Please follow these instructions carefully to ensure optimum results.</span></p>\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\n<p><span style=\"font-size: 14px;\"><strong>TONIGHT, AND FOR THE NEXT 2 DAYS: Sleep Sitting up at 30 to 45 degrees angle.</strong></span></p>\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\n<p><span style=\"font-size: 14px;\"><strong>DO NOT SHAMPOO FOR 48 HOURS AFTER SURGERY.</strong></span></p>\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\n<p><span style=\"font-size: 14px;\"><strong>ALL MEDICATIONS NEED TO BE TAKEN AFTER EATING FOOD TO AVOID NAUSEA&nbsp;and STOMACH UPSET.</strong></span></p>\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\n<p><span style=\"font-size: 14px;\"><strong>DO NOT DRIVE OR DRINK ALCOHOL WHILE TAKING PAINKILLERS OR SLEEPING MEDICATIONS.</strong></span></p>\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\n<p><span style=\"font-size: 14px;\"><strong>SHAMPOO &ndash; BABY SHAMPOO</strong></span></p>\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\n<p><span style=\"font-size: 14px;\"><strong>AVOID SEX, CONTACT SPORTS, STRENUOUS&nbsp;EXERCISE, RUNNING, TENNIS, GOLFING and WEIGHTLIFTING for 14 DAYS.</strong></span></p>\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\n<p><span style=\"font-size: 14px;\"><strong>AVOID hitting you head, piggyback your kids and BE CAREFUL getting in and out of cars.</strong></span></p>\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\n<p><span style=\"font-size: 14px;\"><strong>YOU MAY RESUME swimming after 10 days.</strong></span></p>\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\n<p><span style=\"font-size: 14px;\"><strong>DO NOT PICK or FORCE OFF SCABS/CRUSTS. They will generally be gone in 14 &ndash; 20 days.</strong></span></p>\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\n<p><span style=\"font-size: 14px;\"><strong>DO NOT RUB TOWEL OR ANYTHING ON YOUR HEAD FOR 14 days.</strong></span></p>\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\n<p><span style=\"font-size: 14px;\"><strong>DO NOT USE FULL STRENGTH SHOWER ON YOUR HEAD FOR 7 DAYS</strong></span></p>\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\n<p><span style=\"font-size: 14px;\"><strong>DO NOT USE UN-CLEAN WATER ie FROM BATHTUB/SINK</strong>&nbsp;to wash your hair</span></p>\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\n<p><span style=\"font-size: 14px;\">Blot hair gently with soft towel after washing,&nbsp;<strong>DO NOT RUB</strong></span></p>\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\n<p><span style=\"font-size: 14px;\"><strong>DO NOT BEND OVER</strong>&nbsp;from the waist but get down on your knees, if needed, for first 5-7 days.</span></p>\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\n<p><span style=\"font-size: 14px;\"><strong>DO NOT use&nbsp;</strong>Rogaine<strong>&nbsp;for 14 days- post operation.</strong></span></p>\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\n<p><span style=\"font-size: 14px;\">ATP<strong>&nbsp;SPRAY: this promotes rapid healing</strong>.&nbsp;<strong>Keep Refrigerated</strong>. Use every 1-2 hours for first 3 days</span></p>\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\n<p><span style=\"font-size: 14px;\"><strong>AVOID SUN EXPOSURE / SUNBURN FOR 30 DAYS</strong></span></p>\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\n<p><span style=\"font-size: 14px;\"><strong>IF AREA OF TRANSPLANTED HAIR APPEARS WHITE / PALE, UNUSUAL PAIN OR NUMBNESS&nbsp; or BLACK or OOZING with or without pain&nbsp;SEND US PICTURE AS SOON AS POSSIBLE</strong>, as this could mean blood supply compromise, which if diagnosed early can be easily treated by taking Aspirin Tablets (which can be bought over the counter).</span></p>\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\n<p><span style=\"font-size: 14px;\">Please contact us first if possible if you have any urgent worries or problems. In an emergency, we do carry mobile phone and have an answering machine but if you feel you need URGENT medical assistance immediately, then please seek advice from your local GP or 111 to speak to OOH Medical Team for advice or go Accident &amp; Emergency &nbsp;department of local nearby Hospital or if any life threatening emergency or Allergic reaction dial 999. However, most problems are straightforward and part of the normal healing process.</span></p>\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\n<p><span style=\"font-size: 14px;\"><strong>&nbsp;</strong></span></p>\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\n<p><span style=\"font-size: 14px;\"><strong>DAY OF PROCEDURE:</strong> You may wear a baseball / golf cap or like to go home in but&nbsp;<strong>NOT</strong>&nbsp;a tight fitting or woolly hat. We will show you how to put it on but once it is in place, do not take it off again or keep adjusting it, as your scalp will still be numb from the local anaesthetic and it is very easy initially to dislodge or damage grafts without realising it. When you get home, we recommend that you remove the cap, slowly and carefully, whilst watching in the mirror.&nbsp;</span></p>\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\n<p><span style=\"font-size: 14px;\">Do not bend forward too much and be very careful in getting in and out of car</span></p>\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\n<p><span style=\"font-size: 14px;\">&nbsp;You may need to take&nbsp;paracetamol&nbsp;or ibuprofen for the first 24-48 hours. Once the local anaesthetic has worn off, your donor site is likely to feel tight and sore. You will benefit from taking the painkillers regularly, every four to six hours, for the first 24 &ndash; 48 hours, as this will reduce the discomfort to a minimum. You should not drink alcohol for the first 24 hours as this &ldquo;thins the blood&rdquo; and may cause minor bleeding. After the procedure, you may experience slight spotting of blood from the donor site, but this is not unusual, and you should simply press firmly on the area for 5 minutes with the clean swabs provided.</span></p>\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\n<p><span style=\"font-size: 14px;\"><strong>HOW TO CARE FOR YOUR GRAFTS AFTER THE PROCEDURE</strong> <strong>DAYS 1 and 2:</strong></span></p>\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\n<p><span style=\"font-size: 14px;\">On first morning after the procedure (i.e. approx. 15-20 hours after it is finished). Your donor site will be a little sore.</span></p>\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\n<p><span style=\"font-size: 14px;\"><strong>Avoid</strong>&nbsp;scratching or picking the crusting on your scalp as this can dislodge the transplanted grafts.</span></p>\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\n<p><span style=\"font-size: 14px;\"><strong>You should spray</strong>&nbsp;with the saline water bottle/ATP&nbsp;Solution provided onto your grafts&nbsp;<strong>every 1-2 hours for first 2-3 days. KEEP THE SPRAY REFRIGERATED</strong>.</span></p>\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\n<p><span style=\"font-size: 14px;\">It keeps them moist and helps with any irritating / itching. You can take simple pain killers like&nbsp;paracetamol&nbsp;and must avoid any alcohol, do not operate any machinery or drive if you feel drowsy and must keep medication out of reach of children.</span></p>\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\n<p><span style=\"font-size: 14px;\">You may get some forehead or eyebrow swelling over the next few days. This is normal and is to be expected. This can be reduced by &ldquo;taking it easy.&rdquo; You should lie back rather than sit upright if reading or watching TV as this will help any swelling to dissipate away from your face.</span></p>\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\n<p><span style=\"font-size: 14px;\">&nbsp;You will need to sleep using 2 or 3 pillows for the first&nbsp;<strong>3</strong>&nbsp;nights. Try to sleep at 45-degree angle for first 2-3 days with a neck support/traveller neck pillow to avoid part of transplanted area of head rubbing with bed.</span></p>\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\n<p><span style=\"font-size: 14px;\">You may need to use an ice pack (or bag of frozen peas/wrapped in a towel- NOT DIRECTLY) on the grafted area for the first 2-3 days.</span></p>\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\n<p><span style=\"font-size: 14px;\"><strong>DAY 3</strong>: You can now get your hair wet and take off your bandage. Once you have washed your hair, Transplanted and Donor area,&nbsp;</span><br /><span style=\"font-size: 14px;\"> it will be easier to remove the bandage.&nbsp;</span></p>\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\n<p><br /><span style=\"font-size: 14px;\"> <strong>DO NOT RUB!&nbsp;&nbsp;</strong>Use baby shampoo- mixed with water in a pitcher and pour over your head or dip the sponge and apply- use the sponge&nbsp;UP AND DOWN&nbsp;motion, gently blotting grafts<strong>.</strong></span></p>\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\n<p><span style=\"font-size: 14px;\"><strong>DO NOT RUB&nbsp;</strong>with back and forth motion. You may gently rub lightly the extraction area on the back of your head.&nbsp;</span></p>\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\n<p><span style=\"font-size: 14px;\">RINSE&nbsp;gently with clean water from container or very gentle shower.</span></p>\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\n<p><span style=\"font-size: 14px;\"><strong>DAYS 4 -7</strong>&nbsp;You can use baby shampoo mixed with clean water in a pitcher to pour over your head and rinse with clean water afterwards, as you did on 3<sup>rd</sup>&nbsp;day post procedure.</span></p>\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\n<p><span style=\"font-size: 14px;\">You can resume showering your head at lesser power daily which will also help to soften the crusts.</span></p>\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\n<p><span style=\"font-size: 14px;\"><strong>DO NOT SCRATCH OR RUB</strong>&nbsp;the hair transplanted area.</span></p>\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\n<p><span style=\"font-size: 14px;\">&nbsp;Leave your hair to dry naturally,&nbsp;<strong>DO NOT</strong>&nbsp;use Comb, using your fingers to style it, dabbing very gently with a soft towel.</span></p>\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\n<p><span style=\"font-size: 14px;\">You can do this twice or even three times a day for 10 minutes a time. Any forehead swelling will peak now and disappear over the next few days.</span></p>\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\n<p><span style=\"font-size: 14px;\"><strong>DAYS 8</strong>&nbsp;&ndash;&nbsp;<strong>14</strong> This is the first day you can wash your head with shampoo- directly and use shower as normal.</span></p>\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\n<p><span style=\"font-size: 14px;\"><strong>DO NOT RUB!&nbsp;</strong>Let water flow for 10 mints to soften the scabs<strong>.&nbsp;</strong>Apply shampoo and use<strong>&nbsp;FINGERTIPS&nbsp;</strong>in very gentle circular motion on&nbsp;<strong>BOTH</strong>&nbsp;grafts and extraction sites.</span></p>\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\n<p><span style=\"font-size: 14px;\">Again, soak your hair with very gentle lukewarm water for at least five minutes then put some shampoo a large cup mix with water then gently rinse your scalp letting the lather run over your head and slowly moving it over the whole head. leave for a minute and wash off, as above.&nbsp;</span></p>\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\n<p><span style=\"font-size: 14px;\">&nbsp;You should now be shampooing daily with a mild shampoo such as Baby Shampoo same way as described above.&nbsp;</span></p>\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\n<p><span style=\"font-size: 14px;\"><strong>DO NOT RUB</strong>&nbsp;the area until 14 days as advised above.</span></p>\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\n<p><span style=\"font-size: 14px;\"><strong>DO NOT</strong>&nbsp;be tempted to pick at the crusts but don&rsquo;t be surprised if some of the graft hairs come away with the loose crusts. This is perfectly normal. Very gentle hair washing&nbsp;should be carried out daily as his helps to speed up the healing process.&nbsp;<strong>After the crusts are gone, it will look like your transplanted hair are gone as well, which is normal. The roots of the transplanted hair remain embedded under the skin and can take 3-4 months, before you can notice new hair growth.</strong></span></p>\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\n<p><span style=\"font-size: 14px;\">The donor area should now be healing fast. You will need to avoid strenuous physical activity for 2 weeks after surgery e.g. sex, jogging, sport, gym, fast stair climbing, etc.</span></p>\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\n<p><span style=\"font-size: 14px;\"><strong>DAY 14 - 6 MONTHS</strong>&nbsp; Once your donor area heals this will start to feel more comfortable then it is a good time to have a haircut but not too short to begin with i.e. not less than electric clipper setting &ldquo;4&rdquo;. Over the next six months, the individual hairs will start growing through, getting longer each day.</span></p>\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\n<p><span style=\"font-size: 14px;\">Growth and Shedding: For almost all patients the transplanted and adjacent hair falls out gradually from 2-4 weeks following transplantation and usually start growing from 3<sup>rd</sup>&nbsp;or 4<sup>th</sup>&nbsp;month but in small number of patients it may extend even up to 6 months.</span></p>\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\n<p><span style=\"font-size: 14px;\">It is important to realise that the hair doesn&rsquo;t appear &ldquo;all at once&rdquo; but is a gradual, random process, maximum results are achieved by 24 months.</span></p>\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\n<p><span style=\"font-size: 14px;\">Once all the hair has grown to a reasonable length you can treat your hair normally - washing, drying, dyeing, cutting etc.</span></p>\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\n<p><span style=\"font-size: 14px;\">It is normal not to see any growth at all before three months and it often takes six to nine months before thick growth comes through. It is also common for the transplants to initially grow for a few weeks, then shedding later at 4 weeks, before re growing.</span></p>\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\n<p><span style=\"font-size: 14px;\"><strong>REVIEW / FOLLOW UP VISIT</strong>&nbsp;We would like you to return for review at 2 weeks then 6 months and finally at 12 months to check on growth, results, and satisfaction. We can compare your before and after photos and discuss any future hair restoration requirements. This review is mandatory but if it is difficult for you to get to see us, then please keep us informed by telephone or post or email photos over.</span></p>\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\n<p><span style=\"font-size: 14px;\"><strong>NORMAL EVENTS AFTER PROCEDURE:</strong></span></p>\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\n<p><span style=\"font-size: 14px;\"><strong>Swelling:</strong>&nbsp;for first few days is common- Ice packs are unnecessary.</span></p>\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\n<p><span style=\"font-size: 14px;\"><strong>Pinkness or Redness:</strong>&nbsp;This is common for few days to weeks;&nbsp;ATP&nbsp;Spray reduces this.</span></p>\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\n<p><span style=\"font-size: 14px;\"><strong>Itching:</strong>&nbsp;Taking any Antihistamines at bedtime will relieve itching. Antihistamines are available to buy over the counter at most Pharmacies.</span></p>\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\n<p><span style=\"font-size: 14px;\"><strong>Numbness or Tingling</strong>&nbsp;is generally temporary and usually disappear in a few months. It is the result of cutting small nerve ending during surgery.</span></p>\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\n<p><span style=\"font-size: 14px;\"><strong>THE FIRST NEW HAIR APPEAR IN 3 to 4 MONTHS</strong>: Hair Grafts will disappear in 3-4 weeks after procedure. The Follicle Root which is responsible for growth remains under the skin. You must be patient as it will take several months to start growing again and reach styling length</span></p>\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\n<p><span style=\"font-size: 14px;\"><strong>UNUSUAL COMPLICATIONS&nbsp;ASSOCIATED WITH PROCEDURE.</strong></span></p>\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\n<p><span style=\"font-size: 14px;\"><strong>BLEEDING</strong>: apply direct pressure with fingertip or clean gauze provided for 5 mints. If Bleeding continues, apply the same pressure again and Call the Clinic.</span></p>\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\n<p><span style=\"font-size: 14px;\">&nbsp;</span></p>\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\n<p><span style=\"font-size: 14px;\"><strong>RAISED OR RED / TENDER AREA:&nbsp;</strong>if pimple-like appearance occurs a few days of weeks after surgery. Call Office for routine appointment. Apply Antibiotics cream&nbsp;Fucidin/Bactroban&nbsp;(Can be requested from GP) to the area and keep clean.</span></p>\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\n<p><span style=\"font-size: 14px;\"><strong>IF AREA OF TRANSPLANTED HAIR APPEARS WHITE / PALE, UNUSUAL PAIN OR NUMBNESS&nbsp; or BLACK or OOZING or SWELLING with or without pain&nbsp;SEND US PICTURE AS SOON AS POSSIBLE</strong>, as this could mean blood supply compromise, which if diagnosed early can be easily treated by taking Aspirin Tablets (which can be bought over the counter).</span><br /><br /></p>\n<p><span style=\"font-size: 14px;\"><strong>Post Beard/Moustache Transplant:</strong></span></p>\n<p><span style=\"font-size: 14px;\">You should&nbsp;<strong>NOT TRIM or SHAVE for 4 weeks</strong>&nbsp;on the Transplanted area of Beard or Moustache.</span></p>\n<p><span style=\"font-size: 14px;\"><strong>Do</strong>&nbsp;<strong>NOT</strong>&nbsp;wash the transplanted area for&nbsp;<strong>3 days post procedure</strong>.</span></p>\n<p><span style=\"font-size: 14px;\">You can gently wash after the&nbsp;<strong>3<sup>rd</sup></strong>&nbsp;day, as described above.</span></p>\n<p><span style=\"font-size: 14px;\">You can&nbsp;<strong>ONLY</strong>&nbsp;very gently dab the area to dry to let it dry off on its own</span></p>\n<p><span style=\"font-size: 14px;\">Follow Days&nbsp;<strong>1-14</strong>&nbsp;advise as above for washing and cleaning purposes.</span></p>\n<p><span style=\"font-size: 14px;\"><strong>DO NOT RUB</strong>&nbsp;the area with fingers or towel or with anything for 14 days post procedure.</span></p>\n<p><span style=\"font-size: 14px;\">You have to be very careful for&nbsp;<strong>14 days</strong>&nbsp;post procedure to let the transplanted follicle to get fully embed under the skin.</span></p>\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\n<p><span style=\"font-size: 14px;\"><strong>IF UNUSUAL PAIN: Please call us</strong></span></p>\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\n<p><span style=\"font-size: 14px;\"><strong>Advance Hair Implants</strong></span></p>\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\n<p><span style=\"font-size: 14px;\"><strong>Hair Transplant Clinic.</strong></span><br /> <br /><span style=\"font-size: 14px;\"> <a href=\"tel:\">T: 0208 5060748 M: 07538885074</a>&nbsp;&nbsp;<a href=\"mailto:Info@advancehairimplants.co.uk\">Info@advancehairimplants.co.uk</a></span></p>\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\n<p><span style=\"font-size: 14px;\"><strong>THANK YOU.</strong></span></p>\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\n<p><span style=\"font-size: 14px;\">&nbsp;</span></p>\n<p><span style=\"font-size: 14px;\"><strong>&nbsp;</strong></span></p>\n<p><span style=\"font-size: 14px;\"><strong>&nbsp;</strong></span></p>\n</body>\n</html>', 0, 'email', '2020-01-22 15:53:23', '0000-00-00 00:00:00', 0, 0, 0, '', '', 0, 'aftercare', '', '', 0, 1),
                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                           (230766, 0, 'Mortons Neuroma Information MR', 'Information regarding Mortons Neuroma ', '<!DOCTYPE html>\n<html>\n<head>\n</head>\n<body>\n<p><span style=\"font-size: 14px;\"><strong><img src=\"https://crm.pabau.com/cdn/template_archive/4196/template_attachments/93873dde0c810fdb2ea34745b6c99aef.jpg\" alt=\"\" /><br />Mortons&nbsp;Neuroma&nbsp;Information</strong></span></p>\n<p>&nbsp;A Morton\'s&nbsp;Neuroma&nbsp;or neuralgia is an inflamed nerve caught in between the bones in your foot. You might feel like there is a stone in your shoe and this discomfort is usually found between the heads of the3rd and 4th metatarsal bones. You may also experience numbness, burning or a tingling sensation moving to the tips of the toes in this area. These are all common symptoms. Patients often state that taking their shoes off and massaging the area is the only way to relieve their discomfort. This is because the nerve is being compressed and irritated when they walk and by massaging they are spreading the metatarsal bones a little, giving relief.</p>\n<p><span style=\"font-size: 14px;\"><strong>Diagnosis</strong></span><br />Patients with bunions and low arches feet are often sufferers of the&nbsp;neuroma. Confirmation can be confirmed by finding the&nbsp;Mulders&nbsp;click by recreating the discomfort the patient feels by feeling and moving the&nbsp;neuroma&nbsp;between the metatarsals. Ultra sound will also confirm.</p>\n<p><strong><span style=\"font-size: 14px;\">Treatment</span></strong><br />If the nerve swelling is small then a wide shoe with an&nbsp;orthotic&nbsp;insole which spreads the metatarsal bones out as you walk may be enough to reduce the inflammation and prevent the problem. If the nerve swelling is very large, an&nbsp;orthotic&nbsp;may not be sufficient.<br /><br /><strong>Other treatments include use of</strong><br />1 painkillers,<br />2 steroid injections to bring the welling down<br />3 or have the area temporarily numbed for 8 hours using LA.<br />4 Resting the foot and using ice compresses<br />5 Operate to have part of the nerve removed 75% successful</p>\n<p><br /><br /></p>\n</body>\n</html>', 0, 'email', '2020-01-25 07:34:08', '0000-00-00 00:00:00', 0, 0, 0, '', '', 0, 'aftercare', '', '', 0, 1),
