</span><br /><br /><span style=\"font-size: 16px;\">Kind regards,<br /></span><br /><br /><br /><span style=\"font-size: 16px;\">The&nbsp;Dermamina&nbsp;Team<br /><br /><br /></span></td>\n</tr>\n</tbody>\n</table>\n<br /><br />\n<table style=\"width: 100%;\">\n<tbody>\n<tr>\n<td style=\"text-align: center;\">Want to change how you receive these emails?<br />You can&nbsp;<a href=\"[UNSUBSCRIBE_LINK]\">update your preferences</a></td>\n</tr>\n</tbody>\n</table>\n</div>\n</td>\n</tr>\n</tbody>\n</table>\n</td>\n</tr>\n</tbody>\n</table>\n</body>\n</html>', 0, 'email', '2020-05-03 00:43:38', '0000-00-00 00:00:00', 0, 0, 0, '', '', 0, 'confirmation', '', '', 0, 1),
                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                           (235395, 0, 'After Care Electrolysis ', '', '<!DOCTYPE html><html><head></head><body><p>It is important for you to take extra care of the treated area, especially within the first 24-48 hours. Following electrolysis treatment, the area could be prone to infection if not cared for.</p><p>&nbsp;</p><table width=\"690\"><tbody><tr><td width=\"217\"><p><strong>First 48 hours</strong></p></td><td width=\"473\"><ul><li>sunbathing and sunbed treatments</li><li>very hot baths (it is fine to have a warm bath or a shower)</li><li>friction, particularly from tight clothing (wear loose clothing preferably made from natural fibres)</li><li>perfumed body lotions or creams</li><li>deodorants and anti-perspirants for underarm treatment</li><li>following facial treatment; application of make-up (first 4-8 hours only)</li><li>vigorous exercise and swimming in chlorinated water</li><li>It is important that the area is not touched with un-washed hands</li></ul></td></tr><tr><td width=\"217\"><p><strong>After 48 hours</strong></p></td><td width=\"473\"><ul><li>We recommend you use soothing antiseptic aftercare lotion daily for 3-4 days after treatment, which should be purchased from your practitioner.</li></ul></td></tr></tbody></table><p>&nbsp;</p><p>&nbsp;</p><p><span style=\"text-decoration: underline;\"><strong>Normal Post Treatment Reactions</strong></span></p><ul><li>slight redness in the treated area</li><li>slight swelling in the area</li><li>mild heat sensation in the area</li><li>occasional, tiny crusts around the follicle opening particularly after the first few treatments</li></ul><p>&nbsp;</p><p><span style=\"text-decoration: underline;\"><strong>Speak to Your Practitioner</strong></span></p><ul><li>If redness persists for more than 48 hours</li><li>If large or honey coloured crusts develop in the area</li><li>If pustular spots appear in the area</li></ul><p>&nbsp;</p><p><span style=\"text-decoration: underline;\"><strong>Skin and Hair Management</strong></span></p><p>Remember that electrolysis works, but;</p><ul><li>It is progressive; after each treatment, any hair that regrows will be sparser, finer and lighter</li><li>Hair grows in cycles and only the first cycle provides the results</li><li>To achieve successful treatment, your skin needs to be in good condition and moist</li><li>In between your initial appointments you may need to use some form of hair management at home. Cutting (scissors or razor) is the only method you should use.</li></ul><p>&nbsp;</p><p>If you are concerned or unsure about any aspect of your treatment, please contact your practitioner.</p><p>&nbsp;</p><p><strong>Telephone Alison: </strong>07403460777</p><p><strong>Email</strong>: evolvebeautyandaesthetics@gmail.com</p></body></html>', 0, 'email', '2020-05-08 00:49:42', '0000-00-00 00:00:00', 0, 0, 0, '', '', 0, 'aftercare', '', '', 0, 1);
